    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-05-10T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-05-10T18:00:00-05:00" n="796"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d796">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.01/5–1049: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister-Counselor of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Clark</hi>
                    </persName>), <hi rend="italic">at Canton</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-05-10T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 10, 1949—7 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>TelCan 160. Emb Paris has forwarded inquiry from Fr FonOff re steps US Govt
                    expects take in event Chi Govt moves capital from <pb facs="0698" n="688"
                        xml:id="pg_688"/> Canton. Fr Emb Washington has indicated Fr considering
                    recalling Chargé from Canton and assigning diplomatic officer “of lesser rank”
                    to follow Govt, presumably to Taipei. Dept has informed Fr that decision not yet
                    reached but will be made at proper moment in light <hi rend="italic">inter
                        alia</hi> of location new capital, Ur comments requested.<note n="43"
                        xml:id="d796fn43">For Minister Clark’s reply, see his telegram Cantel No.
                        379, May 14, noon, <ref target="#pg_316">p. 316</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
